title: no-fry fries
directions: Lightly coat a 15x10x1-inch baking pan with cooking spray. Cut potatoes lengthwise into thin wedges. Place in a plastic bag. Spray wedges with nonstick coating. Combine cheese, paprika, and pepper. Add seasonings to bag; close bag. Shake to coat potatoes with seasonings.
Arrange potatoes in a single layer in prepared baking pan. Bake in a 425 degree F oven for 30 minutes or until crisp and fork-tender, turning once. Season potatoes with salt. Makes 4 servings.
Per Serving: cal. (kcal) 155, Fat, total (g) 3, chol. (mg) 4, sat. fat (g) 1, carb. (g) 29, fiber (g) 3, pro. (g) 5, sodium (mg) 103, Percent Daily Values are based on a 2,000 calorie diet
